When he is compiling his Second Book the writer looks outside the ‘domus’ but thinks primarily of property that lies close at hand. Specially he has to speak oi Chesterton. Now Chesterton was part oi the ancient demesne os the Crown. We begin with an extract from Domesday Book which describes it as domim'ca villa Regis (p. 75). This handsome manor passed into the hands os the Prior and Canons.
